               <p>158. <persName id="def1-158-18501125" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-158-18501125" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-158-18501125" type="age" value="24"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-158-18501125" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-158-18501125" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">WILLIAM SMITH</hi>
                  </persName>
                  <rs id="t18501125-158-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18501125-158-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="breakingPeace"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18501125-158-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="wounding"></interp>, feloniously cutting and wounding <persName id="t18501125-name-895" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18501125-name-895" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18501125-name-895" type="surname" value="ASHTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18501125-name-895" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18501125-158-offence-1 t18501125-name-895"></join>John Ashton</persName>; with intent to do him some grievous bodily harm.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18501125-name-896" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18501125-name-896" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18501125-name-896" type="surname" value="ASHTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18501125-name-896" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN ASHTON</persName>
                  </hi>. I keep the Prince of Wales, Woolwich. On 9th Nov., about half-past eight o'clock, there was some sappers fighting in my room—I went and separated them—the prisoner and three of his comrades were there, but they had nothing to do with the disturbance—they were in the passage—one of them was going into the tap-room as I came out—he swore he would be revenged on some one—I said, "There has been quite disturbance enough, my man; be quiet"—he struck me, and we both went down in the passage—the prisoner and his comrades were outside, striking with sticks—Smith tore down the top half of the door, and entered the bar, and struck my wife with a stick, on the head—his com<lb></lb>rades said, "Break the door down, and fetch the b——out; if we get him outside, we will kill him"—I was struck by some one—my wife struck the prisoner with a stick—he took the stick from her, and struck me on the head—my head was cut open—I cannot say whether the prisoner did that—he had been drinking, but was not drunk.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18501125-name-897" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18501125-name-897" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18501125-name-897" type="surname" value="ASHTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18501125-name-897" type="given" value="RHODA"></interp>RHODA ASHTON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of the last witness. I was in the bar, and heard a noise—three soldiers attacked my husband—one knocked him down—I pulled him into the bar, bolted the door, took the staff down, and told the prisoner if he entered the door, I would knock him down—he dragged the door till he got it open—he pulled the bottom of it to pieces—he entered, and I made a blow at him—he took the staff from</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="185011250173"></xptr>
               <p>me, and struck my husband—the others rushed in with sticks to drag my husband out—I was hit both by a stick and a staff—I saw my husband's head bleeding profusely—I cannot say which blow caused it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18501125-name-898" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18501125-name-898" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18501125-name-898" type="surname" value="WALKER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18501125-name-898" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN WALKER</persName>
                  </hi> ( <hi rend="italic">policeman, R</hi> 298). I took the prisoner—he made his escape for about fifty yards; he fell; I retook him—he had been drinking, but knew what he was about—Ashton was in a dreadful state.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> There were fifty or sixty men fighting; they were pretty nearly all intoxicated.</p>
               <p>
